Text: Time...to end this!
...Is this what passes for training in the Garden?

What was it you said, that not even 30 combatants
have completed this training course at maximum
difficulty?

But if you just know where to take breathers, well,
you can see the results.
Hey, Omega—

Lambda, you've clearly made what amounts to a
relaxing stroll, not a training curriculum.

Making an effort not to break your recruits is
important, true, but I think you've gone a tad
overboard, don't you?

Omega! Training at the Garden is not some game where
you get ahead by finding loopholes!

Not everyone is as clever and skillful as you. Even
your familiarity with magic from the treatment
of possession is—

Heh... I've heard the smallest dog barks the most,
but it seems cheeky wolves are the loudest of all.

...And what do you think of what this cheeky wolf
had to say? I was simply speaking frankly as a
fellow Number.

I foresaw that you'd complete the Garden training
course without difficulty.

You're a Number who has accustomed herself to the
magic of possession through real combat in Velgalta,
even before returning to Alexandria—

I'll put the process of your hard-won growth on the
battlefield, and your valuable feedback, to good use
in the Garden's training program.
Very good, Lambda. You're so smart!

...But enough about that for now.
This misunderstanding of yours needs to be corrected.

You completing the training course easily does not
mean the members of the Garden are under-skilled.

Oh dear... Are you perhaps thinking of proving your
point by force?

Omega! You may both be Numbers, but that is no way to
speak to the instructor in charge of training—

No need to get riled up over that, Chi. As you said,
there is no hierarchy among the Numbers.

Even just learning the concept of respect through all
she's experienced since joining the Garden is a big
step forward for Omega.

Were you that cruel of a drill instructor that a
former colleague would speak that way to you...?!
Haha, that's not the joke here, Chi.

...No, and I have a mind to prove to you right now
just how not funny it is. This'll add some more
wrinkles around those oh-so-talented but much-
too-angry eyes of yours.
...93! Step forward!

Oho, next is a sparring match against a member of the
rank and—
I'm right here.
What the...?!
She concealed her presence and got in that close—

I had no idea we had anyone of such skill left in the
Garden who wasn't in the Numbers...!

And she's human, not an elf or therianthrope...
So possession really can occur among humans.
You called, Lady Lambda?
93, duel Omega here.
As you wish.

...But if Lady Omega's abilities prove inferior to my
own, may I strike her down?
What?!
Yes, that would be fine.
...Don't mock me!

A perfect model of precise counterattacks and
resetting of distance... How very much like an
instructor.
That stance... Were you an inquisitor in Midgar?!

Begging your pardon, but I am under no obligation to
speak of my past.

I hear that inquisitors wield their blades in a way
that exhausts their opponents, inflicting pain on
them so that they can extract information!

If she's 93, then she's been her longer than me. That
may also mean she's mastered more of the Garden's
sword techniques than I have!
Omega! 93! Begin!
Yes, ma'am!
Hmph... I'll put an end to this farce!
